abstract: Libraries are for shushing, although in the dance, music and theater research collections of the Library of the Performing Arts at Lincoln Center an intent public seldom even sneezes. On Sunday afternoon, however, the library will take on an air of not-at-all unseemly frivolity when the Celebrity Auction returns after a five-year absence.

abstract: A fossil fish tail the width of the finder's wedding band was discovered yesterday embedded inside a dark gray rock, and although everyone seemed pleased, no one seemed surprised. Last year the fossil remains of a flying lizard were discovered at the same site.
